# **TEST CASES**  **Quiz Game**   

| Submitted By | Atresh & Vikram |
| :---- | :---- |
| Submitted To | Mr. Vipin Tripathi |
| Test Case Version | 1 |
| Reviewer  Name | Mr. Vipin Tripathi |

**Goal :** Create a user-friendly quiz platform using Laravel PHP, where users can log in, attempt quizzes, view their results, and log out seamlessly. The focus is on providing a smooth and intuitive experience, allowing users to:

* Access available quizzes easily from their dashboard  
* Attempt quizzes without confusion  
* Instantly get feedback on their performance  
* Clearly see which answers were correct or incorrect  
* Log out securely

## **TC4:Choosing Between Practice Quiz and Category-Based Quiz.** 

| Scenario |  | The user selects a quiz type. |  |  |  |
| :---- | ----- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Remarks:**  |  | The selection page should **clearly differentiate** between the two quiz modes. |  |  |  |
| **Given** |  | The user is on the **quiz selection page**. |  |  |  |
| **When** |  | They select **either "Practice Quiz" or "Category-Based Quiz"**. |  |  |  |
| **Then** |  | The corresponding quiz **starts immediately**.And if **Practice Quiz** is selected, users get **unlimited attempts** without score tracking.And if **Category Quiz** is selected, users choose a category and proceed to a **scored quiz**. |  |  |  |

## **TC6: Answering a Question with Instant Feedback.** 

| Scenario |  | The user selects an answer for a quiz question. |  |  |  |
| :---- | ----- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Remarks:**  |  | There is no need for a manual **Submit Quiz** button. As soon as the user selects an answer, the system automatically checks it and provides feedback in real-time. This helps users know their correctness immediately and keeps the flow continuous. |  |  |  |
| **Given** |  | The user is actively participating in a quiz session.And the user is presented with a multiple-choice question and answer options. |  |  |  |
| **When** |  | The user selects an option as their answer. |  |  |  |
| **Then** |  | The system instantly evaluates the selected answer.And the message or indicator appears, displaying **"Correct\!"** (highlighted in green) or **"Incorrect\!"** (highlighted in red). |  |  |  |
